            </table>
          </div>
          <hr>

          <h2>Side sliding panels</h2>
          <p>MyService utilises animated sliding panels to display specific content to the user. Panels can be activated by buttons or links. Panels are used:
            <ul>
              <li>on the unauthenticated homepage to log in to MyService,</li>
              <li>from within a 'Claims' flow to access help; and</li>
              <li>globally from the 'feedback' link in the top header to provide feedback on MyService.</li>
            </ul>
          </p>

          <div class="example-box">
            <table>
              <tr>
                <td>
                  <button class="uikit-btn panel-btn">Log in</button>
                </td>
              </tr>
            </table>
          </div>

          <hr>

          <h2>'Return to top' button</h2>
          <p>The
            <font color="red">#return-to-top</font> class is applied to an
            <code>
              <font color="red">&lt;a href="javascript"&gt;</font>
            </code> element to create the 'Return to top' button, visible on vertical scroll in the bottom-right of every page across MyService.
          </p>

          <hr>

          <h2>Flow pagination</h2>

          <div class="example-box">
